The paper deals with the capacity of a time-varying channel and the rate distortion function of a nonstationary source, both of which are topics in information theory (cs.IT). The use of waterfilling and reverse waterfilling techniques is also common in signal processing (cs.SP) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the Wigner-Ville spectrum, which is a tool used in signal processing (cs.SP) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses a Szego theorem, which is a result in complex analysis and operator theory, but is often used in signal processing and information theory (cs.SI).
